Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,will kill\NIslamics for Jesus. And I told you about
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.48,0:16:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the lifetime where I killed killed uh we\Nwere both crusaders. And uh he was there
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.39,0:16:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for Allah and I was there for Jesus.\NAnd uh as we killed each other in a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.88,0:16:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,mackerel,\Nwe went out of body and both burst into
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.75,0:16:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,hysteria. It was so funny. It was\Nhysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.95,0:16:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget it. I said, "Jesus, I\Ndid it for Jesus." He said, "I did it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.48,0:17:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,for Allah.\NWell, it was an important point. We both
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.16,0:17:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,knew it too that we transcended a really\Nmax
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.88,0:17:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,uh point of the evolution of\Nconsciousness. So, uh periodically
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.60,0:17:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout time we've been buddies. You\Nknow, when he needs somebody to kill me
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.40,0:17:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or I need somebody to kill, he\Nvolunteers and we do each other in and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.36,0:17:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend that level.\NSo, that's love of the highest kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.31,0:17:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If it helps you reach enlightenment,\Nof course, you can't do it that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.48,0:17:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to give them a fierce fight\Nor it's not real. So, within this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.79,0:17:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, all those things to us are\Nvery, very real. And if they're not
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.40,0:17:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,very, very real. Cuz if you realize this\Nis a game board, it's not very real to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you anymore. And you can't get the\Nlesson out of it that you were seeking.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to actually be terrified of\Ndeath in order to walk through death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.08,0:18:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you realize it's a game, you can't\Ndo that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.44,0:18:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, we're going to talk about love to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.52,0:18:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the degree that we're able to talk about\Nlove today. And if love takes over, we
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.67,0:18:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,may or may not continue talking about\Nlove.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.96,0:18:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As those states, it's best to have close\Nfriends around you if you're really
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.03,0:18:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,going into spiritual work. Seriously,\Nit's advisable to have family, friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.24,0:18:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,be in an ashramm or at least have\Nspiritual friends who are able to be of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.60,0:18:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,assistance should you become\Nincapacitated, which is quite possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.76,0:18:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd uh sometimes you don't know how
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.76,0:18:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to get here, but your\Nfriends put you in a car and they put
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.96,0:18:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,coffee in your hand and they drive you\Nhere. So that's how you get here. And
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.79,0:18:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then Nico meets you at the door. It's\Nbetter to have somebody at least over
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.48,0:19:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,200 lb who weighs through the crowd. So\Nassistance appears magically uh you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.24,0:19:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,know. All right. So we're going to talk\Nabout the various understandings of love
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the various reflections of love\Nbecause most people are more loving in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.64,0:19:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,more ways than they realize.\NUh they're unconscious of it. This the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.79,0:19:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,other day somebody\NI was polishing. There was this chrome
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.72,0:19:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,around the top of the stove and it was\Nclean but not really shiny. So I took a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.55,0:19:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,steel wool and I started scrubbing it\Nlike that and then it shown like that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.84,0:19:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said now you see it shines with\Nlove.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.03,0:19:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So love takes many forms doesn't it?\NDuty uh commitment uh caringness about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.16,0:19:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,everything.\NYeah. I know. Love for your body. You
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.76,0:19:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,know, you've got to love this thing. And\Nuh if you don't, your wife complains
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.24,0:19:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,bitterly that you don't look nice. So,\Nif you fail it, somebody will remind you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.32,0:20:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to feed it and all the things that\Nnecessarily go with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.91,0:20:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, love takes many many expressions. It\Ntakes the form of caringness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.76,0:20:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,See, we we look at love as some maybe\Nadvanced state and oh, we're not there
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.44,0:20:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,yet. No, that's not so love is constant\Nin our life. See, because nobody is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.55,0:20:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,completely at one level or another. See,\Nlet's you say, well, this guy's at 125,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.55,0:20:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can't know what this is like. No,\Ncertain aspects of them do. And and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.79,0:20:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,those aspects show up in certain aspects\Nof life. So, we begin to nurture those
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.44,0:20:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,aspects and appreciate those aspects of\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.76,0:20:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And which is love is taking a form not\Nusually labeled at love. You see in our
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.79,0:20:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,world love you know denotes romance.\NDenotes here and there. Denotes a me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.67,0:20:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,loving you and a you loving me.\NAnd that kind of love can be lost. It
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.67,0:21:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,can be won or gained or lost or taken\Naway from you. And so that's a different
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.52,0:21:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of love than spiritual love, which\Nis the awareness of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.67,0:21:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a reality that is within you at all\Ntimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.91,0:21:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So in reality, love is a way of being in\Nthe world. Love is actually a style, a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.55,0:21:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,way of being. It's a way of holding\Nyourself and life and every aspect of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.08,0:21:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,life within an overall context. And that\Noverall context gives it a different
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.00,0:21:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning, significance,\Na different appearance. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.67,0:21:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It is just as important to polish the\Nchromium
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.96,0:21:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is to save the life of somebody\Ndying by the side of the street. You
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.00,0:21:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,understand? It's just that capacity\Ntakes this form here. It turns over the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.32,0:22:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,beetle that's on its back here. Here it\Nsaves somebody who's leading by the side
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.00,0:22:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of the street and calls 911.\NAnd here it helps you in the door so you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.24,0:22:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,can get through. You see what I'm\Nsaying? So it's that it's that capacity,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.60,0:22:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that willingness to be that to the\Nworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.72,0:22:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One has no idea of how that is going to\Nbe expressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.24,0:22:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be explaining something to\Nsomebody. It may be um telling them how
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.08,0:22:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to get to 33rd and form. Then you say\Nhow do you get to 33rd and form from
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.08,0:22:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,here? You see\Nyou go here and you go there and you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.60,0:22:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,then you can't get to 33rd and form from\Nhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.96,0:22:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get to there from here. No.\NSo we see that love takes um a thousand
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.24,0:23:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,different forms often unrecognized as\Nwhat it is. As one gets more spiritually
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.28,0:23:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,committed and advanced, you know, you\Nbegin to recognize its expression and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.67,0:23:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to see love everywhere.\NAnd as you get into certain states, the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.24,0:23:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty and perfection of all things\Nand the the constant presence of love
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.03,0:23:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes somewhat staggering.\NAt that point, it may be somewhat
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.76,0:23:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult to function in the world\Nbecause everything
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.79,0:23:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,reflects this beauty and\Nconsequently one has a tendency to break
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.36,0:23:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,into tears.\NSo as you get into let's say the high
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.76,0:23:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,500s there's a phase a phase in which\Nyou cry all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.12,0:23:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,people think you're sad and it's quite\Nthe opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.79,0:24:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because everything is so exquisitly\Nbeautiful that the beauty of the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.00,0:24:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,beauty of love. So beauty and love are\None in the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.79,0:24:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is loving is beautiful. That\Nwhich is beautiful is an expression of
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.48,0:24:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,love. Because divinity as it expresses\Nitself in perfection
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.15,0:24:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in the lower levels one doesn't see\Nperfection. What does one see in the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.24,0:24:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,lower levels? One sees\None sees all of this down here because
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.91,0:24:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,these are all your own projections.\NYou constantly see that there's nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.79,0:24:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,worth anything in the world. Uh you see\Nthat everything is sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.40,0:24:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see everything is frightening.\NUh here you want everything. Here you're
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.88,0:24:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,mad about everything.\NHere you're arrogant about everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.79,0:24:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then so you don't give to get the\Nlecture and give the lecture until you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.52,0:25:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,get the courage.\NI said this morning we're going. No, she
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.15,0:25:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,said this morning we're going\Nand here if you get here or you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.48,0:25:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all the same.\NLife doesn't depend on one thing or
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.44,0:25:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,another. So neutrality you really reach\Nby detaching from things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.64,0:25:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday Kitty of course every lecture\NI give you the recent thing on kitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.76,0:25:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Orange Kitty uh to to be dramatic\Ngets jealous of this affair and the day
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.32,0:25:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,before yesterday afternoon disappeared.\NThe whole staff, everybody, everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.15,0:25:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of preparing for the lecture is\Nscattered all over the landscape looking
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.15,0:25:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for the kitty\Nand there was a screen a big hole on the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.27,0:25:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,screen. That's how Kitty got out. So\Nanyway, Kitty was found and the day was
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.79,0:26:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,saved.\NBut you know, as everybody was out there
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.48,0:26:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,calling Kitty Kitty, Kitty doesn't come\Nto his name. So, but it keeps people
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.91,0:26:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for a kitty feeling good.\NActually, the kitty was discovered by
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.24,0:26:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the people we work with closely.\NAnd u
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.88,0:26:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what I was talking about.\NSo it was necessary to re-release on
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.76,0:26:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitty. In other words, let Kitty go and\Nlet go any attachment to Kitty. And so
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.76,0:26:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,if Kitty was found, it was wonderful.\NAnd if Kitty was not found, it was okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.91,0:26:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And um so you see those losses, what we\Nlook at as losses are all opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.00,0:26:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to let go of attachments. So yesterday I\Nhad a chance to let go of any attachment
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.03,0:26:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that has developed over the years with\NKitty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.60,0:27:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So if Kitty was lost, it was okay. And\Nif Kitty was found, it was very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.24,0:27:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see to move up, we we move into\Nwillingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.24,0:27:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. The whole spiritual direction is\Nbased on willingness. the willingness to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.00,0:27:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of attachments such as I did with\NKitty yesterday just to make sure I
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.79,0:27:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't attached to Kitty.\NThe willingness to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.84,0:27:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nmake the sacrifices that are necessary,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.60,0:27:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to apply that which you\Nlearn.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.76,0:27:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So all all of spiritual direction then\Ndepends on a certain willingness and the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.20,0:27:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,probably the most important willingness\Nis the willingness to surrender things
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.96,0:27:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to God.\NSo people say willingness about what?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.96,0:27:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to surrender things\Nbecause the obstacles to love are all
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.72,0:28:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,attachments to that which is unloving\Nand the willingness to surrender them
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.12,0:28:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and let go of the attachment.\NSo the pathway of devotion then is a
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.39,0:28:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,willingness to constantly surrender\Nanything and everything. It becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.36,0:28:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,extreme.\NThe willingness to sacrifice all one's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.67,0:28:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,positions, titles, money.\NLet go of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.44,0:28:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,all that this world has to offer.\Nlimousines and estates and titles and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.27,0:28:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,membership in great societies etc and\Nwalk away from all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.27,0:28:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is a classic stage in spiritual\Ndevelopment
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.03,0:28:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what do we call it where you let go of\Neverything in the world walk away from
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.24,0:28:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it renunciation. Yeah. So we then come\Nto willingness will eventually take you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.96,0:28:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to renunciation.\NRenunciation takes the form classically
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.96,0:29:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in some pathways\Nas literally renouncing the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.60,0:29:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,literally walking away from the world,\Nmoving out to the middle of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.88,0:29:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and living on a cot with a box, a\Ncandle, and trucking manure
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.44,0:29:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,at 40 bucks a truckload. That's\Nhysterical.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.55,0:29:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And um anyway, it can take the form of\Nthe willingness to renounce everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.00,0:29:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And most people who've been at spiritual\Nwork for some time have usually let
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.55,0:29:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,everything go several times.\NYou walk away from it all. Start from
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.44,0:29:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,zilch. And as time goes on, it begins to\Naccumulate around you again. And so you
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.15,0:29:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then you go through another big letting\Ngo.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.72,0:29:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, like right now, because I'm\Nwriting and I'd like certain references
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.27,0:29:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that I vaguely remember from somewhere\Nin time, but usually book readers who
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.00,0:30:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,live in the 400s want references in the\Nback with page numbers and stuff. You
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.00,0:30:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,know, you can't just tell them uh the\Napherisms of Paneli or something like
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.55,0:30:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that, they want to know published by\Nwhat page.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.88,0:30:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, they're missing the whole point\Nof it, but the if you get the point of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.76,0:30:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,it, you don't look at any references.\NBut anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.52,0:30:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So renunciation then can take the form\Nof walking away from everything. I threw
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.24,0:30:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,up my whole spiritual library.\NWalked away from it all. Walked away
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.88,0:30:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from my medical library. Walked away\Nfrom all those things. And now when I
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.15,0:30:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,need a reference, I I have to have Sonia\Nlook it up on the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.24,0:30:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I remember what it's about and\Nit's just a point I want to make in a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.44,0:30:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,reference. But now they expect it in the\Nreference. So having let go all one
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.08,0:30:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual library, all one's pictures of\NJesus and all that stuff, you know, you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.76,0:30:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,walk away from all that as it's\Ntrappings. Trappings, you say that's all
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.67,0:30:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,trappings, incense and sandals and\Npictures of Jesus and Buddhas and all
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.08,0:31:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that stuff. Throw them all out. They\Nthrow out Buddhas and Jesus and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.24,0:31:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody.\NThey're just pictures. They just
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.24,0:31:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,depictions. They're they're not the real\Nthing. You know what I'm saying? So you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.72,0:31:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,walk away from it and you feel clean and\Npure and wonderful,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.67,0:31:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but then you got to have something to\Ndrive around in. So then you get a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.88,0:31:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you got\Nyou have to have a garage for the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.72,0:31:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you want to go shopping every\Nday, you got to have a refrigerator. So
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.84,0:31:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you all this stuff begins to accumulate\Nagain
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.15,0:31:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and you say, "I don't know how I'm going\Nto do it in this world." cuz you you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.76,0:31:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,know you forgot you got this thing here\Nand uh it's entertaining but it has
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.12,0:31:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,certain needs like like the kitty you\Ngot to give it food in the morning I
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.12,0:31:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,feed the kitty and I feed this here I\Nhave my coffee kitty has the food so
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.12,0:31:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we're both happy\Nif you don't do that it falls over
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.55,0:32:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you get weak\Nsometimes I say to Susie I said I'm so
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.88,0:32:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,weak I can't even walk from here to\Nthere
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.24,0:32:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,said well If you eat something that\Nwould help.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.32,0:32:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I still find it hard to believe that you\Nhave to eat something. I really don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.08,0:32:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And days like today, I just live on\Nliquids and food. It's horrible. So, um
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.32,0:32:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what were we talking about? We were\Ntalking about renunciation. Okay. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.96,0:32:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,renunciation then\Nuh meanings let means letting go of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.08,0:32:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,worldliness. Worldliness, craving,\Nwanting. So you're trying to transcend
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.27,0:32:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the solar plexus. Wanting things is\Ncoming out of the solar plexus. I want
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.60,0:32:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,this. I want that. You I mean Walmarts\Nis the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.15,0:32:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,cathedral of wantingness.\NI love Walmarts. You walk down. Yeah. I
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.27,0:32:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,always talk about Walmarts because it's\Nour new cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.79,0:33:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a certain divinity there. It's\NGod expressed as everything you could
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.39,0:33:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,want. God says, "You want all these\Nthings? Here they are." You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.15,0:33:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Walmart is a present from God to the\Nsolar plexus of humanity. And
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.84,0:33:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,not just the solar plexus, but you got\Nto keep this thing going. Means you got
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.20,0:33:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to wash it, you got to get soap, you got\Nto get things to put the soap in, you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.51,0:33:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,have to have refrigerators, all that\Nstuff. So Walmart is uh very helpful to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.32,0:33:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,survival.\NAnd uh I always speak well of Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.03,0:33:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So renunciation then takes\Nthe form of letting go of what the world
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.20,0:33:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,chases after. Success, money, power,\Nthese are very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.36,0:33:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,See the things that you do at what you\Nwhat you consider beginning levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.20,0:33:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,spirituality. Oh no, they're not\Nbeginning. That's the test at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.48,0:34:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The last lecture we're going to give you\Nwhat the test is like at the end. The
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.88,0:34:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,test at the end had been learned early\Nin the game. I'd let go any desire for
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.39,0:34:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,power.\NSomebody said, "You want power?" I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.72,0:34:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"What for? It's a drag."\NYou try being president of the United
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.24,0:34:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,States or the pope, man. I\NIf you live 24 hours, it's because of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.80,0:34:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the security around you. I mean, you\Nknow, there's nothing worse than having
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.67,0:34:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,power. So, when that temptation comes at\Nthe end, you've refused it years before.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.44,0:34:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You laugh at the Lucifer temptation.\NAll power is yours. Claim it. What are
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.20,0:34:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you, Joker?\NLucifer's best shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.56,0:34:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So those things that will come to you\Nlater under a different form
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.00,0:34:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and very profoundly powerful as they\Ncome when you get very very advanced
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.67,0:34:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,these things are going to come back to\Nyou. So these lessons we learn here are
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.24,0:35:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,powerfully important.\NIf you can let go of the kitty you can
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.20,0:35:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of anything.\NAfter I let go of Kitty, Kitty Gors
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.59,0:35:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,reappeared\Nand found by uh friends and people we
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.40,0:35:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,work with and love.\NSo renunciation is really an inner. See,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.80,0:35:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when you renounce the world,\Nthat's u put it where your mouth is. Put
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.72,0:35:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,your duke swap and let's see if you're\Njust saying that or if you really mean
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.20,0:35:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it. Can you really walk away from it\Nall? And when I first came to Sedona,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.96,0:35:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,most waiters and people around here were\Npeople who had done that. This was a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.24,0:35:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,mecca for the spiritually inspired\Nand the population was three or 4
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.76,0:35:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,thousand. And u\Nmost of the waiters and stuff in the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.80,0:35:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,restaurants had once been president of\Nso and so corporation and
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.83,0:36:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sedana was full of people who were once\Nwealthy, powerful, all kinds of titles
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.72,0:36:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and said hell with it. No, they walked\Naround in sandals and long hair and went
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.56,0:36:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,home all day\Nand their family thought they'd gone
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.32,0:36:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,nuts and uh you better see a doctor. So\Nthe spiritual madness can take you over
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.48,0:36:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and you walk away from everything. And\NI've done it a couple times, walked away
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.59,0:36:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from it all.\NThen it comes to you and it's more
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.96,0:36:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,pristine understanding that renunciation\Nis an internal affair. Renunciation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.04,0:36:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,means the willingness to surrender\Nwithin yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.07,0:36:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your cherished positionalities\Nand more importantly to surrender the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.72,0:36:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,juice you get out of these\Npositionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.83,0:36:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,See the reason you can't transcend the\Nego is because you get such wonderful
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.16,0:37:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,juice out of it. Being mad, being angry,\Nbeing furious, being right, being just.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.72,0:37:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You watch the Middle East, the glee with\Nwhich they kill each other. I mean, they
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.40,0:37:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,love it. You know what I mean? Like an\Nidiot, you're going to go over there
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.44,0:37:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with a peace peace thing. The first\Nthing going to do is kill you because
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.07,0:37:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,any idiot who goes there with his peace\Nis going to ruin the whole game. There
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.04,0:37:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't a single person there that is\Ninterested in peace. Except the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.96,0:37:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,peacemongers\Nwho get all their publicity and power
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.48,0:37:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from selling everybody peace.\NYeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.32,0:37:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill them pieces, man. They're ruining\Nour business.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.88,0:37:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the whole racket is based on\Nanything but peace. And you want to come
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.20,0:37:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in and blow their whole racket?\NLike asking Dillinger to give up crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.20,0:37:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what would he do without Robin\NBanks? You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.40,0:37:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Robin Banks was dealing to his whole\Nthing, right? And after these miraculous
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.35,0:38:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,escapes, what was he doing within 48\Nhours? He was robbing a bank. I'll say
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.00,0:38:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to these bank robbers, "What'd you do\Nwith the last money you had? 3 days ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.52,0:38:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they got 48,000. 2 days ago, they got\N14,000. I mean, have you spent it all or
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.00,0:38:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what?\NAre you broke?"
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.16,0:38:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Robin Banks is what he does. That's\Nwho he is. That's his thing, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.80,0:38:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're going to hold up a parade that\Nsays stop robbing banks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.64,0:38:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Right.\NThe way we transcend the limitations of
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.44,0:38:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego and its positionalities is it\Ngets such a tren tremendous payoff. And
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.56,0:38:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this is where willingness really comes\Nin.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.00,0:38:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to be honest with\Nyourself that the reason you cling to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.59,0:38:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,this is because of the payoff you're\Ngetting out of it. It's hard to admit
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.04,0:38:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that you like hating people.\NFirst of all, they deserve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.35,0:39:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And hating them is a secret way of sort\Nof getting even with them. You having
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.44,0:39:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the little hate thoughts out there. They\Nwin their way through and stab the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.52,0:39:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,person. You say, "Oh, I want to think of\Nthat. That's like a witch would think
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.00,0:39:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that." But that's what you're up to,\Naren't you? Little stabbing thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.83,0:39:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief. People hang on to grief for\Nlifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.20,0:39:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,About everything that's possible that\Ndie has died around me. How long you
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.40,0:39:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,going to hang on to the grief about\Nthat? I'll tell you how long to keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.48,0:39:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,About one second. Let it go the instant\Nhappens.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.32,0:39:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let it go. Surrender it completely\Nand totally to God the instant it
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.11,0:39:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,happens.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.20,0:39:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because you develop the capacity to\Ndo that. So the reason for spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.28,0:39:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,training then\Nis you develop a powerful capacity to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.64,0:39:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of anything\Nand you never know when it's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.64,0:40:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,come up. So and so just died.\NYou just let go that instant. The minute
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.80,0:40:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you the minute the phone message comes\Nin,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.72,0:40:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you let it go.\NYou don't grieve about it 30 years
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.28,0:40:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,later. You don't celebrate every\Nanniversary of the death of Cuckoo, your
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.80,0:40:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,little bird. Then the next two weeks\Nlater, it's you got to celebrate the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.20,0:40:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,birth of Uncle Lou. And then a month\Nlater, it's a time to to celebrate the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.83,0:40:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,death of a Then your mother's death\Ncomes up. The anniversary of all this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.56,0:40:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as you get older and older, the\Nwhole calendar is the anniversaries of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.72,0:40:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,crap.\NWe're going to keep pumping 911 forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.92,0:40:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We already we already got December 5th,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.92,0:40:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. Then you got 1776. We got the end\Nof World One. Then we got November 11th.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.35,0:40:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget November 11th at 11:00 a.m.\NWhen I grew up, November 11th, 11:00
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.00,0:41:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a.m. was Armistice Day. We all held our\Nheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.35,0:41:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a beautiful value to it. I'm\Njust talking about the diamond side of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.40,0:41:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it. It's one thing to give respect and\Nsend love to all those people
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.59,0:41:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and to do so\Nout of reverence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.56,0:41:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?\NWe're talking about the fact that what
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.72,0:41:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,makes these things tenacious\Nis first of all you're trained in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.16,0:41:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Your mind thinks this way. But after\Nyou're aware that you're trained in them
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.31,0:41:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and your mind thinks this way and you\Nsee the absurdity of the idea of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.04,0:41:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,causality, you'll find that your mind\Nstill wants to do this. And you see, why
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.88,0:41:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is my mind still doing that when I know\Nbetter? And a spiritual student usually
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.44,0:41:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,goes into that. I know better. How come\NI'm still hating that guy and want to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.88,0:41:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,get even with him? Why did I give him\Nthe finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.72,0:42:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you the pleasure. I got the first\Nand only time I ever did it in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.59,0:42:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It was terrific. I can see why those\Nguys are out there throwing stones at
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.88,0:42:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the Jews and the Jews are throwing at\Nthe Arabs and everybody's wanting to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.56,0:42:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,kill each other. I mean, it's terrific.\NTake that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.76,0:42:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's a high like uh\Nbeats riding buck and Broncos. You know
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.68,0:42:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what I mean? Got more drama. You see\Nthose guys out there at a rodeo
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.52,0:42:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a whole bunch of them\Nsitting behind me and they they've all
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.80,0:42:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,their own casts.\NAll of them cast. They've all got
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.31,0:42:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,all cripping up from from riding riding\Nthese bulls, you know. Can't wait to get
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.80,0:42:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,on the next one.\NThe juice you get off of that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.59,0:42:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the guy's got he's had six\Nfractures over the last five years
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.16,0:43:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,riding bulls,\Nand he's going to get right back on the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.40,0:43:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,next bull.\NOh my gosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.56,0:43:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Extreme sports, huh?\NAll right. So willingness then because
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.11,0:43:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that's one really important aspect of\Nlove. It's willingness is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.68,0:43:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,really take you up here because\Nwillingness is going to
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.35,0:43:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,give you the motivation to accept\Nthings.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.96,0:43:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also going to take you past reason\Nwhich is the big roadblock.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.16,0:43:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The big roadblock. Most of the people\Nthat go into spiritual work are usually
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.07,0:43:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 400 I mean many of them the 10\Nlectures like this are usually in the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.83,0:43:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,400s in which reason brings them here\Nand now reason becomes the block because
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.48,0:44:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,very few people to get to love\Nwe said love to transcend the 400s is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.92,0:44:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,accomplished by about 4% of the\Npopulation 4%. Whoa. To get to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.40,0:44:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional love is 0.4%.\N0.4%. Where's the numbers that go on all
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.88,0:44:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,this stuff? Oh, here they are.\N4%.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.52,0:44:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,At 540.4%.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.56,0:44:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So we talk about love a lot but as a to\Nrealize uh one's identity as that which
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.11,0:44:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is the source of life itself\Nis not all that easy to
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.72,0:44:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I would not say achieve but that easy to\Nrealize
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.88,0:44:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore I I I mentioned the things\Nthat I think can be useful that are
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.59,0:45:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,generally available not everybody can go\Noff and join the Nashim. Not everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.72,0:45:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,can walk away from their family and\Ntheir job etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.72,0:45:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can this do go then? So the\Nwillingness to let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.44,0:45:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,positionalities, the willingness to\Nsurrender
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.68,0:45:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,not the things themselves but the\Nattachment to the things themselves. You
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.72,0:45:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to give up your Cadillac.\NUm but you let go of its former meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.48,0:45:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to you.\NYou let go striving for success because
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.28,0:45:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize the truth is the is the\Nepitome of success. To realize the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.52,0:45:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of where you are.\NSo renunciation then means eventually an
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.31,0:45:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,inner renunciation.\Nthe the willingness to let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.80,0:45:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,insisting that if a thing is isn't\Nlogical, it can't be true and all these
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.04,0:46:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of positionalities.\NThe willingness to then uh let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.96,0:46:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that stands in the way of\Nlove.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.88,0:46:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As we do that, we find that uh the\Nthings that keep coming up that block us
