Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.00,0:46:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To be unwilling to let go attachment to\NKitty would mean grief, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.40,0:47:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd be setting yourself up for grief.\NI lose the cat. Lose the cat. Tonight's
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.92,0:47:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be awful. Tomorrow I won't be\Nable to lecture. I'm just going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.48,0:47:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,grieving and weeping and nashing my\Nteeth. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.59,0:47:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the un unwillingness then is\Nwhat sets you up for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.28,0:47:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You say to yourself, am I willing to set\Nmyself up for this or let it go? Now
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.20,0:47:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes it a little more real,\Ndoesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.31,0:47:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're willing to let it go for some\Nairy fairy sounding thing like the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.07,0:47:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,presence of God, which sounds good, but\Nwho knows what that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.28,0:47:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you might be willing to let it go\Nbecause if you don't, this is where
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.80,0:47:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to end up. End up\Ndown the scale suffering from
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.20,0:47:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you see wantingness is an endless\Nsuffering, isn't it? Because
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.24,0:47:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,wantingness, the constant wanting things\Nis constantly setting you up with
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.04,0:48:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,desire. You're always wanting something.\NI only have one want left in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.80,0:48:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep it there. I cherish it.\NOne worldly want.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.48,0:48:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, "God, can't I have just one?\NI don't really have it, but I have a
